net.jhoogland.jautomata

Interface Automaton<L,K>

  • Type Parameters:
    L - label type
    K - weight type (Boolean for regular automata and Double for weighted automata)
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    MTAutomaton<T,L,K>, ReverselyAccessibleAutomaton<L,K>, Transducer<I,O,K>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractAutomaton, AcceptorIntersection, ArrayAutomaton, ArrayMTIntersection, Closure, Concatenation, Determinization, EditableAutomaton, EpsilonRemoval, EpsilonRemoval.EpsilonAutomaton, ExplicitAutomaton, HashAutomaton, HashMTIntersection, HashTransducer, Intersection, KTropicalSemiringConversion, LabelConversion, MTIntersection, MTLabelConversion, Push, ReversedAutomaton, Reweight, SemiringConversion, SingleInitialStateOperation, SingleStringAutomaton, TransducerComposition, TransducerLabelConversion, UnaryOperation, Union

    public interface Automaton<L,K>
    All automata (acceptors, transducers, multi-tape automata, and their weighted variants) implement this interface. The methods initialStates(), transitionsOut(state), initialWeight(state), finalWeight(state), from(transition), to(transition), label(transition), and transitionWeight(transition) define the automaton. The method semiring() returns the Semiring over which the automaton is defined. The method topologicalOrder() makes it possible to specify a topological order on the automaton states, if it exists. Some algorithms are faster if a topological order is specified.
    Author:
    Jasper Hoogland
